                      <span>37</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2000-05-17</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>This book has a very unusual copyright notice. By using the information in this book, you implicitly enter into an agreement with Sun microsystems where any clean room Java implementations you write, from scratch, have to  be submitted to Sun for conformance testing. I did not discover this until  years after I bought the book. This kind of a  "contract-by-fait-accompli" is illegal and unenforceable, but it  may still be a pain to deal with. I suggest the Meyer and Downing book  instead, since it is unencumbered.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Excellent reference for the JVM</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
